04ff1f2f-c7be-46cb-b69c-59840fc052a5.06c16e33-a68d-4578-a577-a2a4ece0c96c.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
04ff1f2f-c7be-46cb-b69c-59840fc052a5.169d4888-9f18-4348-8442-6a2de8a725da.callout=CLU internal global\: caller\=HPOO 04ff1f2f-c7be-46cb-b69c-59840fc052a5.57ec1a57-7842-4382-a142-d051437f8e67.description=
Runs an SSH command

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
port - The port number for running the command. It overwrites the port given inside the host input -in a syntax like host\:port-, if this exists.
command - The command to execute.
arguments - The arguments to pass to the command.
pty - Whether to use pty (true, false. Default is false).
privateKeyFile - Path to private key file, relative to ICONCLUDE_HOME on the RAS.
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of user. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
timeout - Time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete (optional, default 90 seconds).
characterSet - The characterSet name for input stream encoding from the target machine. For example, SJIS, EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8. 
closeSession - Close SSH session at completion of this operation (true, false)? If false the ssh session will be cached for future calls of this operation during the life of the flow. If true the ssh session used by this operation will be closed. Default is true.

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Extra Results\:
STDERR - The STDERR of the command.
STDOUT - The STDOUT of the command.
04ff1f2f-c7be-46cb-b69c-59840fc052a5.6d8b6021-a0be-4fc2-b06e-0c09bdae98a7.description=
Operation to check for null or empty string local variables.

Inputs\:

inputList\:  comma seperated list of variables to check

Reponsses\:
hasNull\:  at least one variable is null or has an empy string for a value
noNulls\:  all variables have a value

Result\:  List of variables that are null or empty strings

04ff1f2f-c7be-46cb-b69c-59840fc052a5.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO, running on HPNA.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script example on sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab is running here\:  /data01/clu_direct/${scriptName} ${scriptArgs}

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Javascript operator converts local HPOO variables into "index1\=value1 index2\=value2..." format
3) Operator runs SSH to HPSA\:2222, which uses Rosh to execulte shell on HPNA running CLU (tied to HPNA for credentials, etc)

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
device_username	- username -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
device_password	- encrypted password -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.
router		- Device target IP or DNS

Results\:
 flowOutput - Raw data back from ssh/telnet to $router commands

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

Efficiency\:
checkForNull \= 0.016s
runCLU \= 10.241s
 - Connect to "sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab" and initiate Expect \= 7s
 - Init CLU \= 0s
 - Actual Commands against Router\: 3s
Cleanup .1s
